<br>
I recently smithed, for the first time anywhere in the game, all of the Black Lace-Boned armour except for the belt.  See my post on these boards.  Be the first person IN GAME to wear this armour.  Supply quest is an option for Beastlords too, with slightly different supplies, as outlined below.<br>
 <br>
All items above are made after you order them, unless you get lucky and I have got one lying around.  <br>
<br>
I offer a discount from the above prices (high end market price) for each blue diamond you bring me.  <br>
<br>
Trade Supply Quest<br>
<br>
In lieu of the cash amounts outlined above, I will accept trade skill supplies in the quantities outlined below. <br>
<br>
<br>
For all pieces except Leggings, Tunics, and Cloaks, the deal is this.  You bring me 4 times the trade skill supplies I need to make the item.  We group.  You get 3 attempts at your armour piece.  Regardless of success or failure, I keep the supplies for the fourth attempt as my fee.  If  I succeed on the first combine, I retain all of the remaining supplies as my fee.  If I succeed on the second combine, I retain all of the remaining supplies as my fee.  If I succeed on the third combine, I retain the supplies for the fourth attempt as my fee.  If I fail on the first 3 combines, I still retain the supplies for the fourth attempt as my fee.  <br>
<br>
Chances are I will succeed within your three attempts.  When I smith my wisdom is over 255 and my strength is also over 255.  My current skill is 245, but is raised to 255 with me Grandmaster smithee's hammer.  255 is the highest smithing skill you can reach with a skill enhancing item.  250 is the highest skill you can reach without the hammer.  According to EQ Traders, folks are succeeding 33% to 50% on these combines.  I have not yet had anyone walk away sans the item we were attempting to make.  <br>
<br>
Trade Supplies:<br>
<br>
Helanic Tundra Armour:<br>
<br>
Veil, collar, bracers, and boots:  (Total needed for 4)<br>
<br>
4 blue diamonds, 4 Acids, 4 leather paddings, 4 frost tempers, 4 Celestial Essences, 2 Large Bricks of Velium, 4 Coldain Velium Tempers, 6 Large Bricks Medium Quality Ore, 4 Imbued Ivories, 4 molds (sold in Halas).<br>
<br>
<br>
Helm, Pauldron, Girdle, Sleeves, Gloves:  (Total needed for 4 attempts)<br>
<br>
8 blue diamonds, 8 Acids, 4 leather paddings, 4 frost tempers, 8 Celestial Essences, 4 Large Bricks of Velium, 4 Coldain Velium Tempers, 12 Large Bricks MQ Ore, 4 Imbued Ivories (4 molds).<br>
<br>
<br>
Large Bricks of Medium Quality Ore are sold by venders, but not in all cities.  Closest city to Halas selling MQ ore is Qeynos.  Acid is also sold by some, but not all, smith venders.  Because Halas is a dry village, none of the venders in Halas sell Acid.  Warning, Acid does not stack.<br>
<br>
Large Bricks of Velium drop off of various mobs in Velious.  3 small bricks can be combined to produce one large brick.  For every 3 small bricks you bring in lieu of a large brick, add one Coldain Velium Temper.  <br>
<br>
Coldain Velium Tempers are sold by dwarfs in Thurgadin.  My price (max ally with 126 Charisma) is just under 27 plat per temper.  <br>
<br>
Frost tempers and celestial essences are player created items.  Each frost temper requires brewing 2 essence of winter, one ice goblin blood, and one brandy (triv 135).  Each celestial essence requires combining celestial solvent (sold in SH) and a spell research component in a mortar and pestle (no fail combine).  Ivory is a drop only gem that must be imbued by a tribunal-worshipping shaman.  I will provide all of the frost tempers, celestial essence, and imbued ivory needed for your 4 supply sets (3 for your attempts, 1 for my fee) for an additional fee of one blue diamond.  <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Helanic Tundra Breast Plate, Cloak, and Leggings:<br>
<br>
For Leggings, Tunics/Breastplates, and Cloaks the deal is this.  You bring me 6 times the trade skill supplies I need to make the item.  We group.  You get 4 attempts at your armour piece.  Regardless of success or failure, I keep the supplies for the fifth and sixth attempts as my fee.  If  I succeed on the first combine, I retain all of the remaining supplies as my fee.  If I succeed on the second combine, I retain all of the remaining supplies as my fee.  If I succeed on the third combine, I retain all of the remaining supplies as my fee.  If I succeed on the fourth combine, I retain the supplies for the 5th and 6th combine as my fee.   If I fail on the first 4 combines, I still retain the supplies for the fifth and sixth attempts as my fee.    <br>
<br>
I am asking for 6 sets of supplies to maximize your chances of getting your breastplate, leggings, or cloak.  These items have a higher triv, so failures are more likely.  Additionally, the more blue diamonds I have to process into rings, the more blue diamonds I am likely to lose.  Each blue diamond must go through a pottery combine, a brewing combine, and then a smithing combine just to produce the rings used to make armour.  Each armour piece uses either one, two, or three rings.  So even before we get to the final combine in the Northman forge stage, some blue diamonds are likely to be lost.  <br>
<br>
<br>
For 3 ring items, the success rate is still reported at around 33%, so chances are reasonable that I will succeed within your four attempts.  When I smith my wisdom is over 255 and my strength is also over 255.  My current skill is 245, but is raised to 255 with me grandmaster smith's hammer.  255 is the highest smithing skill you can reach with a skill boosting item.  250 is the highest skill you can reach without the hammer.  <br>
<br>
<br>
